Diagram 2 (Black's Good Move)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 seems to be a strong move.
\par However, black 2 is a good response.
\par If white plays at 3, black answers at 4 and lives.
\par
\par Instead of 1, even if white made a placement at 3, black still answers at 2.
\par
\par Now you noticed where the vital point is, didn't you?
\par }
