Diagram 4 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Once white 1 and black 2 have been played, it is calm for white to cut at 3. This move aims at creating a shortage of liberties.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj If black plays 4, white pushes at 5 and this is it! Black cannot play at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 .
\par }
